FT: Oxford City 3 St Albans City 1. Play-off hopes ended for Saints with National League South defeat. Report online now at Herts Ad Sport.
86' McEachran now replaced by Coyle. 3-1
85' Noble booked for what can only be described as a tap tackle. Fine in rugby, yellow in football. 3-1
84' First Oxford sub. Clark off and Owusu on. 3-1
78' Jeffers fires a cushioned volley back across goal and just past the post. Close but really needed that to go in. 3-1
Poor defending again followed by a fine finish that left Johnson stranded. The changes will be blamed but Saints had to go for it. Still do but the season is falling apart quick. 3-1
72' GOAL! OXFORD CITY! 3-1. Ewan Clark #NationalLeagueSouth
70' Triple sub for Saints. Sole, Banton and Noble on with Lankshear, Dawson and Wiltshire sacrificed. St Albans' season boils down to this. 2-1
From his typical range too, about a yard out after the ball had been nodded back across goal. Sucker punch for Saints who now need to cut loose. 2-1
68' GOAL! OXFORD CITY! 2-1. Joe Iaciofano #NationalLeagueSouth
66' Banton being readied. Who he replaces will be a sign of whether this is the first twist from Allinson. Sole might be coming on too. 1-1

65' OFF THE LINE! Neal got away down the right and his cut-back was pushed into the middle by Jeffers. It found Goddard and although he picked his spot to the left of Dudzinski, Rowan scrambled it away at the last moment. Remains 1-1
62' Johnson denies Iaciofano with a single-hand save. Angle was rapidly closing on the former Saint but still a good save. 1-1
60' And there's the record (I believe). Wiltshire booked which gives him the most yellow cards in a season for St Albans City. Obvious one too, a tug back. 1-1
57' Jeffers bounces Carroll to the floor and his curled effort is spilled by the keeper. He gets the rebound though before Weiss arrives. Only Banton warming up for Saints. 1-1
55' Dawson with an effort that was a bit of a cross and a bit of s shot but lacked power or direction for either and Dudzinski gathers. 1-1
53' Lankshear still struggling but no sign of Bender or anyone else being readied on the bench. 1-1
49' Saints were temporarily down to 10 men after Lankshear picked up a knock. Looked like a dead leg possibly. 1-1
There's more to it than this, number of wins could come into it. More on that later if needed.
46' St Albans City restart the game drawing 1-1 at Oxford City.

If the scores stay as they are elsewhere but Saints win, the scenario is scarily simple for the final day. Havant and Chippenham would have to draw with each other and City would need to win by four clear goals. They need to win here first though.

HT: Oxford City 1 St Albans City 1. Two fine strikes and a game that is in the balance. Saints need to win though and with the results elsewhere, they need to start putting the ball in the net and improving their goal difference. Time to twist rather than stick
45+1' Rowan now booked for Oxford after blocking off a run from Neal. 1-1
44' Goddard caught out but Oxford can't get the pass right. Game is there for the taking if either side want to take the bull by the horns. 1-1 #NationalLeagueSouth
38' Carroll talks himself into a booking after Neal had brought a good save out of Dudzinski. 1-1 #NationalLeagueSouth

28' Oxford' turn to go close as Clark bends one just wide form the right side of the area. Giving Lankshear a tough time over there. 1-1 #NationalLeagueSouth
26' Goddard now almost scores again but his shot from the left side of the area is blocked behind by Rowan. Corner comes to nothing. 1-1 #NationalLeagueSouth
Came after a decent passing play. Jeffers had a shot blocked but City worked it back to the edge of the area where Goddard curled one into the top corner. 1-1 #NationalLeagueSouth
25' GOAL! ST ALBANS CITY! 1-1. John Goddard #NationalLeagueSouth

21' Lankshear a lucky boy there. Took a chance with a tackle on Iaciofano and missed the ball completely, clearly hitting the striker's legs. He stayed up though and there were no appeals. Was technically a foul though. 1-0 #NationalLeagueSouth

19' McEachran is being allowed to dictate the game here. One-two on the edge of the box just runs away from him to Johnson. Saints offering nothing so far and lacking any urgency. 1-0 #NationalLeagueSouth
17' Jeffers down after an innocuous challenge. Don't know if he landed badly. No movement on the bench though so will be fine to continue. 1-0 #NationalLeagueSouth

I'm supposed to say that it was a superb solo goal and technically it was but the Saints defence and midfield want slapped with a wet fish. McEachran was allowed to run all the way to the edge of the box without a yellow shirt coming close. Good run, good finish, awful defending
13' GOAL! OXFORD CITY! 1-0. Zak McEachran #NationalLeagueSouth

10' Both sides have just got into prime crossing positions and both have given an example of how not to do it. Neal put his put for a goal kick, via the corner flag, while Harmon's effort was ballooned high and out. 0-0 #NationalLeagueSouth
6' Oxford's two forwards are Benyon and Iaciofano, both once of the St Albans parish. Both sides probing in a very muted atmosphere. 0-0 #NationalLeagueSouth
4' First chance comes after a corner for Oxford. Harmon snatches at it from the edge of the area and slices it over the top. 0-0 #NationalLeagueSouth
1' St Albans City attacking from left to right in the first half. Oxford City have kick-off. 0-0 #NationalLeagueSouth

It's a tall order and made all the more difficult by the fact Havant and Chippenham, the only other sides in the race for seventh, play each other on the final day. Havant hold the aces at the minute, four points ahead of City. Chippenham are a point better off.

St Albans City at Oxford City for me today and it's all about maths and probability. Still so many variables but it really boils down to Saints needing to win their last two games, and improving their goal difference by a cumulative margin of at least six wouldnt harm either.

89' Sub for Carlisle. Ellis off, Mellor on. 2-1 #LeagueTwo
88' GOAL! STEVENAGE! 2-1. Luke Norris (pen). Sends the keeper the wrong way. #LeagueTwo
Caught me by surprise. Tussle in the box...
87' PENALTY to Stevenage...
86' Kristian Dennis replaced by Tyrese Omotoye for Carlisle. 2-0 #LeagueTwo
Lovely goal. Ball slid in from the left-hand side by Jack Armer. Missed the sliding Patrick but not the sliding Alessandra who diverts it home at the far post. 2-0 #LeagueTwo
63' GOAL! CARLISLE UNITED! 2-0. Lewis Alessandra #LeagueTwo
62' Double sub for Stevenage. Carter and Lines ready to go in place of List and Upson. Feels like this could be Carter's last chance to shine. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
57' Sub for Carlisle. Scorer Riley picks up a knock and is replaced by Alessandra. 1-0 #LeagueTwo

55' Big opportunity to equalise for Upson after being found by Norris inside the box and unmarked. Had to time to pick his spot but went too close to Howard and the keeper pushed it out. 1-0 #LeagueTwo

Something happening now. Riley flashes in a shot from the right side of the area that goes across Pym and into the far corner. Patrick had kept the ball from going out for a throw just before the cross. Riley had time without anyone closing him down and picked his spot. 1-0
53' GOAL! CARLISLE UNITED! 1-0. Joe Riley  #LeagueTwo
51' Might have a little snooze before the drive back. Nowt happening of note. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
46' Carlisle United restart the contest at Brunton Park, drawing 0-0 with Stevenage. #LeagueTwo

HT: Carlisle United 0 Stevenage 0. End of season fare of the highest order. One chance for Boro that hit the post. One cross from Carlisle that hit the bar. Hosts have been slightly ahead in possession but denied often by good blocks, usually from Prosser. Dull though. #LeagueTwo
43' Prosser with another block before a shot from distance bounces wide. Defender has been excellent in the first half. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

38' James-Wildin puts his mates under a whole heap of unnecessary pressure with a loose pass deep just outside his own box. Patrick wriggles into space for a shot but Prosser males the vital block. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

33' Taylor booked. Didn't need to make the tackle either. Carlisle had an overlap and should have been in on goal but their final pass was poor. Taylor was always going to be second to the ball but was back to cover. Daft. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
24' And now List hits the top of the stand from 18 yards. Another good chance and Boro really can't afford to be passing these up. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

24' What a chance that was for Boro. Ball found its way to Norris inside the box who managed to turn the bounce to his advantage. However, as he is about to shoot he swings and misses from the corner of the six-yard box. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

20' Cuthbert, Norris and Reid link up well in the Carlisle box and feed it to Taylor about 16 yards out. Was a body between him and the goal but instead of shooting, he attempted to play it back to Reid who was never going to reach it. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
18' Carlisle having all the possession at the minute but despite putting  couple of crosses into the Boro box, Stevenage are defending fairly comfortably. Not many shots on goal like. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

7' POST! Think it was Prosser with the header at the back post. Went back across goal, not overly quickly, but away from Howard in the Carlisle goal. Bounces off the upright and Reid's rebound attempt is blocked. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
5' Great tackle by Upson prevents Patrick from having a shot from just inside the area. Ball runs loose and Pym is out quick to smother any rebound. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
2' Pym confident that a cross from the left was going to cause no problems. Bounces off the top of the bar... 0-0 #LeagueTwo
1' Stevenage will kick towards the Warwick Road End in the first-half here at Brunton Park. They start too against Carlisle United. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

FT: Mansfield Town 2 Stevenage 0. Promotion party in full effect for confident Stags. Boro just off the pace. Report going online at Comet Sport now #LeagueTwo
90+3' GOAL! MANSFIELD TOWN! 2-0, Matty Longstaff. Too much space for a player of his quality. Low shot leaves Pym stranded.
90+1' Final Mansfield sub. Bowery for Murphy. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
87' Andrade booked for Boro and Hawkins on for Oates. Second Mansfield change. 1-0
86' Murphy stings the palms of Pym with a shot from the edge of the area. 1-0 #LeagueTwo

82' Vancooten has been suffering with a back injury for the last few minutes and can't continue. Boro have used all three subs too so they are down to 10 for the remainder. Bostwick into defence. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
Attendance: 5,086 (73 from Stevenage)
@SFC_Interviews Very true but never looked like he was going to get in the right position to score though. The hard work will please Evans mind you.
74' Ball falls to the sub after a decent free-kick from Lines had been headed towards him. Snatched at it slightly and it sails well wide. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
72' Andrade on for List too. Final Boro change. Not a great game from the number seven. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
72' Sub for Mansfield. Maris replaced by Wallace. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
60' Second Boro sub. Lines on for Read. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
59' Akins now given too much space on the edge of the box to turn. Fortunately his shot was well off target. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
56' That was better build-up from Stevenage but the cross only became a good one after a defensive error. First touch though allowed O'Toole to recover and Bishop gathered. 1-0 #LeagueTwo
54' Akins now pulls a shot across goal and just wide. The home side have started strongly and Boro are being pushed aside with ease at the minute. 1-0 #LeagueTwo

Awful defending from Boro. Corner came into the middle and there was at least one swing and miss from a Boro player. Fell to Lapslie 10 yards out and central and he simply side-footed it home. 0-1 #LeagueTwo
51' GOAL! MANSFIELD TOWN! 0-1. George Lapslie #LeagueTwo
50' Sub for Stevenage, Daly on for Norris. Didn't look overly injured but physio did look to apply ice straight away. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
46' Mansfield start with a chance which Maris curls low through a crowd and beyond the far post. Not sure if he was expecting someone to attack it but nobody did. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
46' Mansfield Town restart the second half drawing 0-0 with Stevenage in #LeagueTwo
It's like the Wheeltappers & Shunters Club in here, I tell thee.

HT: Mansfield Town 0 Stevenage 0. Boro may have nothing to plat for but pride but Mansfield do. Their play-off place is under threat. Neither side shining tonight though. Poor passing, no real chances. #LeagueTwo
43' Taylor goes into the book for dissent I think. Did foul Maris but wasn't yellow worthy. Started chirping at the ref as soon as the whistle went though. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

37' Loud boos after Boro shout for a penalty but that is just because public enemy number one has just stood up down below the press box. Can't see the touchline from my seat but don't need to do a meerkat impression to find out. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
36' Norris robs McLaughlin on the right and his low shot is palmed away by the keeper for a corner. Was on target. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
35' Coker down receiving treatment but looks OK to continue. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

32' It's a little bit meh at the minute. Some good positions for both teams at times but passing in general is poor. Neither team stringing anything together and neither enjoyed sustained pressure. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
23' Good defending by McLaughlin to head an Arthur Read cross behind for a corner from in front of his own goal. Jamie Reid was lurking. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
21' Maris goes into the book now for the most obvious yellow of the season. Cleans out Read as Boro looked to  break. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

17' Longstaff must be wondering what the hell he has done wrong. Mansfield break, he gets clear down the right and the pass to him is so far in front. A talented kid but is being poorly utilised so far tonight. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
15' Perch takes a booking rather than run. Taylor had pushed the ball round him so the ex-Newcastle man simply pushes him over. Most obvious yellow of the season. 0-0 #LeagueTwo
14' George Maris sends a shot from distance high over the top. 0-0 #LeagueTwo

11' Longstaff getting into plenty of space for Mansfield. Passes to him have been woeful but James-Wildin and Cuthbert will need to keep an eye on him. They lurve Steve Evans here too... 0-0 #LeagueTwo
